The shell script seems to be hanging. When I run heritrix, I see two
processes in the shell, a Java -DHeritrix and a /bin/sh Heritrix
process. The Java heritrix process unloads and the crawl ends, but the
sh script still hangs and never unloads, it just keeps outputing a
dot. I&#39;m just gonna bypass the shell script altogether, just wanted to
see if there was a simple solution to this problem, because its
happening on two different machines. 

-Ahnu

